na Elias","date":"November 30, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Bakr ibn Hafs reported: Ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, while travelling between Mecca and Medina would not withhold his food from a leper, nor an outcast, nor anyone afflicted, even letting them sit with him at his table. Source: al-Zuhd wal-Raqa\u0304\u2019iq 611 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0628\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34966,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/17\/aishah-humility-deathbed\/","url_meta":{"origin":21276,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Death: Aisha\u2019s Godfearing humility on her deathbed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 17, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Mulaykah reported: Ibn Abbas asked permission to see Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, before her death while she was overcome with suffering. Aisha said, \u201cI am afraid he will praise me.\u201d It was said, \u201cHe is the cousin of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28987,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/umar-humility-raises-wisdom\/","url_meta":{"origin":21276,"position":2},"title":"Umar on Humility: Allah raises his wisdom if he humbles himself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubaydullah ibn \u2018Adi reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said upon the pulpit, \u201cVerily, if a servant humbles himself for Allah Almighty, he will increase his wisdom.\u201d Source: Juz\u2019 fi\u0304hi\u0304 H\u0323adi\u0304th Sufya\u0304n ibn \u2018Uyaynah 24 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21957,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/02\/17\/ibn-mubarak-knowledge-rest-life\/","url_meta":{"origin":21276,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Mubarak on &#8216;Ilm: Seek knowledge for the rest of your life","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 17, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Nu\u2019aym ibn Hammad reported: Ibn al-Mubarak, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cA man will continue to have knowledge as long as he is seeking knowledge. If he assumes that he has knowledge, he has become ignorant.\u201d In another narration, it was said, \"For how long will you seek\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40115,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/14\/revealed-humility\/","url_meta":{"origin":21276,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Humility: Believers must be humble to each other","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 14, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah has revealed to me that you be humble to one another and not transgress against each other.\u201d Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 4214 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35117,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/01\/tuba-faults\/","url_meta":{"origin":21276,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Humility: Blessed is one busy with self-improvement","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBlessed is he who is occupied with his own faults over the faults of people.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 6237 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0647 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645 \u0637\u064f\u0648\u0628\u064e\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","wid